author: Sammy Batten - Staff writer
title: College football: Saturday's Big 5 matchups
text:
College football: Saturday's Big 5 matchups By Sammy Batten - Staff writer 
Boston College (3-1, 0-1) at Duke (3-1, 1-0) 
Time: 3:30 p.m. 
TV: Fox Carolinas 
The bulletin board: Two of the nation’s top defenses meet in Duke’s homecoming game. ... Boston College leads the nation in total defense, limiting foes to 118 yards per game. The Eagles are second in scoring defense (7.8). ... Duke is 10th nationally in total defense (261.0) and seventh in scoring defense (11.5). ... Duke’s Jeremy Cash earned national defensive player of the week honors after making 12 tackles, three tackles for loss and forcing two fumbles in last week’s win against Georgia Tech. ... Pine Forest grad Harold Landry is BC’s top defender and is tied with Cash for the ACC lead in tackles for loss (eight). 
East Carolina (2-2, 0-1) at SMU (1-3, 0-0) 
Time: 4 p.m. TV: ESPNEWS 
The bulletin board: The Pirates are seeking their first American Athletic Conference win. ... ECU leads the series with SMU, 4-2. ... Junior quarterback James Summers rushed for 169 yards and two touchdowns for ECU in last Saturday’s win against Virginia Tech. ... ECU junior Isaiah Jones, from Austin, Texas, is third in AAC receiving with 32 catches for 397 yards and two touchdowns. ... SMU is coached by former Clemson offensive coordinator Chad Morris. 
Louisville (1-3, 0-1) at N.C. State (4-0, 0-0) 
Time: 12:30 p.m. TV: WRAL-5, WSFX-26 
The bulletin board: The Wolfpack starts ACC play against its first Power Five conference foe. ... Wolfpack quarterback Jacoby Brissett leads the nation in completion percentage (74 of 95 for .779). ... Junior Matt Dayes has rushed for 454 yards and nine touchdowns in the first four games for N.C. State. ... The Wolfpack ranks third nationally in total defense, limiting foes to 205.8 yards a game. ... Louisville linebacker Keith Kelsey leads the ACC with 10 tackles per game. 
North Carolina (3-1, 0-0) at Georgia Tech (2-2, 0-1) 
Time: 3:30 p.m. TV: ESPNU 
The bulletin board: The Tar Heels try to end an eight-game losing streak in Atlanta and start their ACC schedule with a win. ... Georgia Tech owns a 28-19-3 advantage in the series against UNC and has won 14 of the last 17 meetings. ... Sophomore Elijah Hood has rushed for 384 yards and three scores in UNC’s first four games. ... Georgia Tech leads the ACC in rushing offense, averaging 326 yards per game. ... UNC ranks last in ACC rushing defense, giving up 228.8 yards. 
Florida State (3-0, 1-0) at Wake Forest (2-2, 0-1) 
Time: 3:30 p.m. TV: ESPN 
The bulletin board: Wake Forest faces the ninth-ranked Seminoles in an ACC Atlantic Division game. ... FSU’s Dalvin Cook leads ACC rushers with 158.7 yards per game. ... Wake Forest tops the ACC in passing yardage (300.0) and is 11th nationally in pass defense (145.0). ... True freshman Kendall Hinton made his first college start in last week’s loss to Indiana for Wake. He leads the Deacons in rushing (45 for 170). Wake’s Brandon Chubb is tied for fourth in ACC tackles with nine per game.
